# The mod fetches these files by sha256 (manifest.json) and writes the downloaded
# bytes to disk verbatim, so the bytes here must stay byte-identical to the bytes
# the mod bundles — which come from the Quartz repo, where the same files are
# LF-normalized. Any CRLF here makes manifest.json's hash unmatchable by a bundled
# file, and the mod re-downloads that language on every fresh install, forever.
#
# eol=lf pins the WORKING TREE, not just the index: `text=auto` alone would leave
# a Windows translator's checkout as CRLF and let them commit it straight back.
*.json text eol=lf
